Fraction absorbed, i.e., only a fraction of the talinolol in the intestinal lumen is absorbed. This parameter determines how much of the talinol is excreted in every round of the enterohepatic circulation.
F_tal_abs of dose is absorbed. (1-F_tal_abs) is excreted in feces.
The effective fraction absorbed is lower, because P-glycoprotein transports part of the absorbed talinol back in the intestinal lumen!.
